Ceramic and Metal Biomaterials: Types, Manufacturing, and Applications | 陶瓷与金属生物材料：类型、制造与应用Ceramic | 陶瓷Ceramic Types &amp; Manufacturing | 陶瓷类型与制造
Traditional Ceramics: Porcelain, Stoneware, Earthenware; each uses unique chemical compositions and raw materials. The Hong Kong/Canton region is known for specialized techniques.传统陶瓷： 瓷器、炻器、陶器；各自采用独特的化学成分和原材料。港粤地区以专门工艺著称。
Manufacturing Process: Clay (powder + water) is shaped, dried (shrinks and reorganizes), then fired/sintered to bond particles.制造过程： 粘土（粉末+水）成型、干燥（收缩与重组）、烧结使颗粒结合。
Materials: Kaolinite and Bentonite clays; Flint and Quartz additives reduce shrinkage; Feldspar creates glossy, non-porous finishes.原材料： 高岭土和膨润土；燧石和石英添加剂减少收缩；长石形成光滑致密表面。

Biomedical Ceramic Classifications | 生物医学陶瓷分类
Bioactive Ceramics: Bond with tissue (e.g., glass ceramics for implant coatings, stimulate hydroxyapatite formation).生物活性陶瓷： 能与组织结合（如用于植入物涂层的玻璃陶瓷，促进羟基磷灰石形成）。
Bioresorbable Ceramics: Biodegradable (e.g., calcium phosphate compounds, hydroxyapatite).生物可吸收陶瓷： 可降解（如磷酸钙化合物、羟基磷灰石）。
Bioinert Ceramics: Minimal tissue interaction (e.g., pyrolytic carbon, alumina for joint replacements and dental crowns).生物惰性陶瓷： 与组织相互作用极少（如用于关节置换和牙冠的热解碳、氧化铝）。

Natural Ceramics in the Body | 体内天然陶瓷
Bone: ~60% minerals (mainly hydroxyapatite), ~26% collagen, plus cells. Cortical (dense) and trabecular (porous) types; bone marrow contains stem and immune cells.骨骼： 约60%矿物质（主要为羟基磷灰石）、约26%胶原蛋白及细胞。分为致密骨和松质骨；骨髓含有干细胞和免疫细胞。
Teeth: Higher inorganic content; layers include enamel, dentin, and pulp. Strength from nanostructured calcium phosphate.牙齿： 无机物含量更高；分为釉质、牙本质和牙髓。强度来自纳米结构磷酸钙。

Sintering Process &amp; Applications | 烧结工艺与应用
Sintering: Occurs at ~⅓ melting point; surface atoms bond without full melting.烧结： 在约熔点三分之一温度下进行，表面原子结合但未完全熔化。
Applications: Thermal spray coatings, porous structures for cell migration, dental crowns (zirconia vs. alumina), hip implants with hydroxyapatite coatings.应用： 热喷涂涂层、细胞迁移的多孔结构、牙冠（氧化锆与氧化铝）、带羟基磷灰石涂层的髋关节植入物。

Overview of Biomedical Materials | 生物医学材料概述
Ceramics: Biocompatible, mainly for implant coatings.陶瓷： 生物相容性好，主要用于植入物涂层。
Metals: High mechanical strength, used for load-bearing implants.金属： 机械强度高，用于承重植入物。

Ceramic Manufacturing &amp; Applications | 陶瓷制造与应用
Steps: Raw material prep, shaping, drying, sintering.步骤： 原料准备、成型、干燥、烧结。
Applications: Dental/orthopedic coatings, surface treatments to minimize protein/cell deposition and reduce friction.应用： 牙科/骨科涂层，表面处理减少蛋白质/细胞沉积和摩擦。

Metals | 金属Types &amp; Properties of Medical Metals | 医用金属类型与性质
Stainless Steel: Affordable, but poor corrosion resistance.不锈钢： 价格低廉，但耐腐蚀性差。
Cobalt-Based Alloys: Better corrosion resistance, but potential carcinogenic ion release.钴基合金： 耐腐蚀性更好，但可能释放致癌离子。
Titanium Alloys: Best biocompatibility and corrosion resistance, non-toxic, but expensive.钛合金： 生物相容性和耐腐蚀性最佳，无毒但价格昂贵。

Special Metal Materials | 特殊金属材料
Shape Memory Alloys: Nickel-Titanium; used in braces, stents, IVC filters; return to shape when heated.形状记忆合金： 镍钛合金；用于牙套、支架、下腔静脉滤器，加热后可恢复原形。
Liquid Metals: Solid at room temp, liquid at body temp; used in wearable electronics (e.g., mercury, gallium).液态金属： 常温为固体，体温为液体；用于可穿戴电子（如汞、镓）。
Biodegradable Metals: Magnesium- and zinc-based; gradually absorbed by the body.可降解金属： 镁基和锌基金属，能被人体逐渐吸收。

Corrosion Issues &amp; Protection | 腐蚀问题与防护
Mechanism: Oxidation, electrode formation, accelerated by moisture/oxygen.机制： 氧化、电极形成，受潮湿/氧气加速。
Biological Impact: Corrosion products trigger immune response and inflammation, may cause bone degradation.生物影响： 腐蚀产物引发免疫反应和炎症，可能导致骨质破坏。
Protection: Use corrosion-resistant metals (chromium, titanium), inert ceramic coatings, and protective oxide layers.防护措施： 采用耐腐蚀金属（铬、钛）、惰性陶瓷涂层和保护性氧化层。


